<item>
            <title>[FELIX-788] Failed to create object that extends super class with BundleContext argument</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-788</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In this situation:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bundle 1:&lt;br/&gt;
public interface I {&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public abstract class A implements I {&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public abstract class B extends A implements Runnable {&lt;br/&gt;
  public B(BundleContext context) {&lt;br/&gt;
  }&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bundle 2:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public class C extends B {&lt;br/&gt;
  public B(BundleContext context) &lt;/p&gt;
{
    super(context);
  }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I used org.apache.felix.iPOJO.Factory.createComponentInstance(null);&lt;br/&gt;
But iPOJO failed to create instance like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;C&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ERROR: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;instance.name&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; createInstance -&amp;gt; The POJO constructor invocation failed : (class: C, method: &amp;lt;init&amp;gt; signature: (Lorg/apache/felix/ipojo/InstanceManager;Lorg/osgi/framework/BundleContext;)V) Expecting to find object/array on stack&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>JDK 1.6&lt;br/&gt;
Felix 1.2.1&lt;br/&gt;
iPOJO 1.0.0 and 0.8.0</environment>
